Medicines that can be taken 
while breastfeeding include:
• most antibiotics;
• common painkillers such 
as paracetamol and 
ibuprofen (but not aspirin);
• hayfever medicines such 
as loratadine and cetirizine;
• cough medicines (provided 
they don’t make you 
drowsy);
• asthma inhalers;
• normal doses of vitamins.
You can use some methods 
of contraception but not all, 
so check with your GP
